The article discusses President Trump's vision of a global trading system that is free of imbalances and unfair practices. It highlights China's violation of fair trade rules since joining the World Trade Organization in 2001, resulting in significant economic growth while the US lost factories and manufacturing jobs. The article also mentions President Trump's efforts to address these issues through tax cuts, deregulation, energy sector development, and trade negotiations. Despite attempts to negotiate with China, their unfair trade practices and theft of intellectual property continue, leading to a growing trade deficit with the US. China's response has been denial and retaliatory tariffs, targeting American farmers. The article emphasizes President Trump's commitment to defending American interests.